(1257, 328, 'work', 'Clinton Paquin is one of the talented Software Developer ninjas at BLITZ.  He excels not only as a PHP/MySQL backend engineer but also as a Front End HTML, jQuery, and CSS developer.   Working within the interactive realm since 2004, he has extensive experience building enterprise level sites and expertise considering security, scalability, and maintainability.  He relishes the opportunity to engineer sites that not only look great, but exceed industry standards in smart semantic markup, page load speed, and mobile first consideration.  Prior to BLITZ, Clinton led teams at Pepperdine University, Apollo Interactive, and ConsumerTrack to architect, develop and implement scalable PHP/MySQL applications and microsite'),
(1258, 328, '_work', 'field_531070c4b8b20'),
(1259, 328, 'life', 'Clinton was born and raised in Southwest Montana and received his Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science from Montana State University (go Bobcats). He played Division II Soccer in college, spent a couple of summer’s commercial fishing in Alaska, climbed Mt. Whitney (the highest peak in the continental US), and did a short stint in the visual FX industry (and has the credits to prove it).\r\n\r\nHe spends his free time enjoying the great outdoors with his beautiful and adventurous wife, Sarah Jon, and their son Cooper. If he’s not at the beach, you’ll find him reading about new technologies, contributing to LA area technology meetups, or cheering on the Denver Broncos and debating the finer points of a good microbrew.'),
